>There is no world building to be done, it's all been done for you
This is really fucking lazy and useless past a short story
Proper worldbuilding works hand-in-hand with the characters. If you take setting X and randomly place a character in it without understanding why they would be the way they are, the story falls apart faster the more you lean into the setting.

The reason some of our more adventurous writefags create large and detailed settings is so they can tailor the setting and characters together. They aren't doing a palette swap with Zootopia or BNA because their characters don't match that place.
OTOH, if you want to write fanfics based on games or existing OCs, fine. Chances are your characterization is utter shit because you assume everyone is as expert at the lore as you. Good fanfic establishes the relevant lore just as if it was an OC setting. The bonus for fans is they might see foreshadowing or hints of existing bits.

tl;dr: lazy writing is always lazy whether your setting is completely original or not
